occurrenceRemarks: Puma encountered dead under shrubs next to a seldom-used forest trail, in second-growth Nothofagus (southern beech) forest. Appeared to be subadult or young adult. Skeleton mostly intact (not disarticulated), save for skull and forelimbs which were moved <1m. Some skin and fur remaining. No obvious cause of death.

occurrenceRemarks: Mountain lion scat deposited in about 5 pieces. Disintegrated due to recent rains. The scat contains stiff white hairs. It's hard to tell depth from these pictures, but the scrape was more than 12 inches long and there was a pile of redwood needles, leaves, and sticks (from the scrape) more than 4 inches high. The scat was deposited on the "hill" made by scraping. Notice the size of this scat relative to the two bobcat scats photographed on the same day. Length: ~10-11 inches Width: ~1 inch Scrape length: >12 inches

occurrenceRemarks: Photos by Dan Sayler: "It snowed just a trace, less than 1/2'' during the dark between Sun. night/Mon. morning, so conditions were perfect in that it was pretty easy to see that no one had been down the road since the weekend.
